diff.description: Returns a list that contains all elements contained in list1, that don't appear in list2
diff.name: diff

distinct.description: Returns a list that contains unique elements from the given list
distinct.name: distinct

flatten.description: Returns a list of all elements from all lists in the given list
flatten.name: flatten

intersect.description: Returns a list that contains all unique elements that are contained by both list1 and list2
intersect.name: intersect

join.description: Creates a string made of all elements of the list separated with the given separator
join.name: join

max.description: Returns the largest element (elements must be comparable)
max.name: max

merge.description: Merges maps. Values in the first map will be overwritten with values from the other one if keys are the same
merge.name: merge

min.description: Returns the smallest element (elements must be comparable)
min.name: min

product.description: Cross joins two lists of maps: eg. product({{a: 'a'},{b: 'b'}}, {{c: 'c'},{d: 'd'}}) => {{a: 'a',c: 'c'},{b: 'b',c: 'c'},{a: 'a',d: 'd'},{b: 'b',d: 'd'}}
product.name: product

reverse.description: Returns a list that contains elements in reversed order from the given list
reverse.name: reverse

shuffle.description: Returns a copy of the list with its elements shuffled
shuffle.name: shuffle

slice.description: Returns a slice of the list starting with start index (inclusive) and ending at stop index (exclusive)
slice.name: slice

sortedAsc.description: Returns a list of all elements sorted in ascending order (elements must be comparable)
sortedAsc.name: sortedAsc

sortedAscBy.description: Returns a list of all elements sorted by record field in ascending order (elements must be comparable)
sortedAscBy.name: sortedAscBy

sortedDesc.description: Returns a list of all elements sorted in descending order (elements must be comparable)
sortedDesc.name: sortedDesc

sum.description: Returns a sum of all elements
sum.name: sum

take.description: Returns a list made of first n elements of the given list
take.name: take

takeLast.description: Returns a list made of last n elements of the given list
takeLast.name: takeLast

toAny.description: Wrap param in 'Unknown' type to make it usable in places where type checking is too much restrictive
toAny.name: toAny

durationBetween.description: Computes Duration between two dates: start date inclusive and end date exclusive
durationBetween.name: durationBetween

isBetween.description: Checks if day is in range <fromInclusive, toInclusive>.
isBetween.name: isBetween

isBetween.description: Checks if day is in range <fromInclusive, toInclusive>.
isBetween.name: isBetween

isBetween.description: Checks if day of week is in range <fromInclusive, toInclusive>. if to < from in ISO standard (numerous from MONDAY), then checks if day of week is in one of ranges <from, SUNDAY> and <MONDAY, to>
isBetween.name: isBetween

isBetween.description: Checks if month is in range <fromInclusive, toInclusive>. if to < from, then checks if month is in one of ranges <from, DECEMBER> and <JANUARY, to>
isBetween.name: isBetween

isBetween.description: Checks if time is in range <fromInclusive, toInclusive>. if to < from, then checks if time is in one of ranges <from, 24:00> and <00:00, to>
isBetween.name: isBetween

localDateTime.description: Returns LocalDateTime based on LocalDate and LocalTime
localDateTime.name: localDateTime

now.description: Returns current time as an Instant
now.name: now

nowAtDefaultTimeZone.description: Returns current time at default time zone as a ZonedDateTime
nowAtDefaultTimeZone.name: nowAtDefaultTimeZone

nowAtOffset.description: Returns current time with given time zone offset as an OffsetDateTime
nowAtOffset.name: nowAtOffset

nowAtZone.description: Returns current time at given time zone as a ZonedDateTime
nowAtZone.name: nowAtZone

periodBetween.description: Computes Period between two dates: start date inclusive and end date exclusive
periodBetween.name: periodBetween

periodBetween.description: Computes Period between two dates: start date inclusive and end date exclusive
periodBetween.name: periodBetween

periodBetween.description: Computes Period between two dates: start date inclusive and end date exclusive
periodBetween.name: periodBetween

toEpochMilli.description: Converts LocalDateTime at given time zone into epoch (millis from 1970-01-01)
toEpochMilli.name: toEpochMilli

toEpochMilli.description: Converts LocalDateTime with given time zone offset into epoch (millis from 1970-01-01)
toEpochMilli.name: toEpochMilli

toInstant.description: Converts epoch (millis from 1970-01-01) into an Instant
toInstant.name: toInstant

toInstantAtDefaultTimeZone.description: Converts LocalDateTime at default time zone into an Instant
toInstantAtDefaultTimeZone.name: toInstantAtDefaultTimeZone

zone.description: Returns time zone with given zone id e.g. Europe/Warsaw
zone.name: zone

zoneOffset.description: Returns zone offset with given zone offset id e.g. +01:00
zoneOffset.name: zoneOffset

zuluTimeZone.description: Returns Zulu time zone which has offset always equals to UTC+0
zuluTimeZone.name: zuluTimeZone

format.description: Render LocalTime, LocalDate, LocalDateTime, OffsetDateTime or ZonedDateTime in ISO-8601 format
format.name: format

formatter.description: Creates DateTimeFormatter using given pattern and locale
formatter.name: formatter

lenientFormatter.description: Creates lenient version of DateTimeFormatter using given pattern
lenientFormatter.name: lenientFormatter

lenientFormatter.description: Creates lenient version of DateTimeFormatter using given pattern and locale
lenientFormatter.name: lenientFormatter

parseInstant.description: Parse Instant in ISO-8601 format e.g. '2011-12-03T10:15:30Z'
parseInstant.name: parseInstant

parseLocalDate.description: Parse LocalDate in ISO-8601 format e.g. '2011-12-03'
parseLocalDate.name: parseLocalDate

parseLocalDateTime.description: Parse LocalDateTime in ISO-8601 format e.g. '2011-12-03T10:15:30'
parseLocalDateTime.name: parseLocalDateTime

parseLocalTime.description: Parse LocalTime in ISO-8601 format e.g. '10:15' or '10:15:30'
parseLocalTime.name: parseLocalTime

parseOffsetDateTime.description: Parse OffsetDateTime in ISO-8601 format e.g. '2011-12-03T10:15:30+01:00'
parseOffsetDateTime.name: parseOffsetDateTime

parseZonedDateTime.description: Parse ZonedDateTime in ISO-8601 format e.g. '2011-12-03T10:15:30+01:00[Europe/Paris]'
parseZonedDateTime.name: parseZonedDateTime

distanceInKm.description: Calculate distance in km between two points (with decimal coordinates), using haversine algorithm
distanceInKm.name: distanceInKm

distanceInKm.description: Calculate distance in km between two points (with decimal coordinates), using haversine algorithm
distanceInKm.name: distanceInKm

abs.description: Returns the absolute value of a value.
abs.name: abs

ceil.description: Returns the smallest (closest to negative infinity) double value that is greater than or equal to the argument and is equal to a mathematical integer.
ceil.name: ceil

floor.description: Returns the largest (closest to positive infinity) value that is less than or equal to the argument and is equal to a mathematical integer.
floor.name: floor

pow.description: Returns the value of the first argument raised to the power of the second argument
pow.name: pow

round.description: Returns the closest long to the argument. The result is rounded to an integer by adding 1/2, taking the floor of the result, and casting the result to type long.
round.name: round

nextBoolean.description: Returns an uniformly distributed boolean value
nextBoolean.name: nextBoolean

nextBooleanWithSuccessRate.description: Returns a boolean value with a success rate determined by the given parameter. Success rate should be between 0.0 and 1.0. For 0.0 always returns false and for 1.0 always returns true
nextBooleanWithSuccessRate.name: nextBooleanWithSuccessRate

nextDouble.description: Returns an uniformly distributed double value between 0.0 (inclusive) and 1.0 (exclusive)
nextDouble.name: nextDouble

nextDouble.description: Returns an uniformly distributed double value between fromInclusive and toExclusive
nextDouble.name: nextDouble

nextDouble.description: Returns an uniformly distributed double value between 0.0 and toExclusive
nextDouble.name: nextDouble

nextInt.description: Returns an uniformly distributed integer value between fromInclusive and toExclusive
nextInt.name: nextInt

nextInt.description: Returns an uniformly distributed integer value between 0 and toExclusive
nextInt.name: nextInt

nextLong.description: Returns an uniformly distributed long value between fromInclusive and toExclusive
nextLong.name: nextLong

nextLong.description: Returns an uniformly distributed long value between 0 and toExclusive
nextLong.name: nextLong

split.description: Splits given text into a list of Strings using given regular expression. Note that trailing empty strings won't be discarded; e.g. split('a|b|', '|') returns a list of three elements, the last of which is an empty string
split.name: split
